data.title: Keen Obituaries
data.text:
Keen Obituaries

Typed and Contributed by Linda Carpenter

Â©2005

KEEN - Sunday morning, July 20, at 8:45 o'clock, at her home, Madison, Mrs. Sara Frances Keen, aged 72 years. Survived by daughters, Mrs. Mattie Branham of Lebanon, Mrs. Sallie Bean, Madison; sons, Oscar, Edgar, Vernon, Walter, Allen and John Keen; brothers, Joe and Charles Eanes; sister, Mrs. Tommie Branham. Funeral services at Ivy Point Church Monday afternoon at 2 o'clock. Nephews will serve as pallbearers. Interment Ivy Point Cemetery. Cole & Garrett, funeral directors. *(Found within the 1936 obituaries.)

KEEN - Thursday morning, April 15, 1943, at a local infirmary, at 5:15 o'clock, Edith Dorris Keen, aged one year. Survived by parents, Mr. and Mrs. Woodrow W. Keen; sister, Dona Mai Keen; grandparents, Mr. and Mrs. John Helton; Mr. and Mrs. John Keen. Remains are at the residence, Edenwold, Tenn. where funeral services will be conducted Saturday afternoon at 2 o'clock by Rev. John Stroud. Interment Spring Hill Cemetery. Cole & Garrett, funeral directors.

KEEN - Sunday morning at 4:15 o'clock, March 9, 1947, at his home, Madison, John Head Keen, age 76 years. Survived by wife, Mrs. Artie Keen; sons, Arthur, Albert, Lewis, Edward and Woodrow Keen; daughter, Mrs. Francis Hunt; 13 grandchildren; brother, Cornelius Keen of Hendersonville; sister, Mrs. Sally Renes of Goodlettsville. Funeral services this Monday afternoon at 2 o'clock at the Ivy Point Church of Christ, conducted by Rev. C. H. Robinson. Nephews will serve as pallbearers. Interment in Ivy Point Cemetery. Cole & Garrett, funeral directors.

KEEN - Monday morning December 12, 1955, at her home on Alta Loma Rd., Nancy Love Keen, age 3 months. Survived by parents, Mr. and Mrs. Lewis Keen; sisters, Mary, Elizabeth, Emma Lou, Barbara Ann Keen; grandmother, Mrs. Artie Keen. The remains are at the home where services will be conducted Wednesday morning at 10 o'clock by Rev. N. Butch Tucker. Interment in Family Cemetery. Cole & Garrett, funeral directors.

KEEN - Friday morning Dec. 8, 1958 at a local infirmary, Thomas Haskel Keen, age 7 weeks. Survived by parents, Mr. and Mrs. Lewis Keen; sisters, Mary, Elizabeth, Emma Lou and Barbara Ann Keen; grandparents, Mr. and Mrs. Campbell Canady, all of Madison. Remains are at Cole & Garrett Funeral Home where prayer service will be conducted Saturday morning at 11 o'clock by Rev. B. Frank? (Black spot on copy.) Interment Cole Cemetery. Cole & Garrett, funeral directors.

KEEN - Edward L. Keen - April 18 - April 20, 1959 (This is all that's written on the copy.)

KEEN - Kel? M. Keen - 7 - 12 - 1960 (All that's written on copy.)

KEEN - Wednesday morning, Oct. 9, 1963, at a local hospital, Baby Boy Keen. Survived by parents, Mr. and Mrs. Edward L. Keen; brother, Terry Keen, Old Hickory; grandparents, Mr. and Mrs. Solomon E. Keen, Joelton, Mr. and Mrs. D. C. White, Grovetown, Ga. Remains are at the Anderson Garrett & Boyd Funeral Home, Joelton, where prayer services will be held Thursday morning, Oct. 10, at 10:00 o'clock by Rev. Carl Martin. Interment Greenville Cemetery. Anderson Garrett & Boyd Funeral Directors, Joelton.
